rning.%20Economists%20expect%20the%20data%20to%20show%20prices%20rose%202.7%25%20on%20a%20year-ver-year%20basis%2C%20slightly%20hotter%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fcpi.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober's%202.6%25%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%20strategists%20said%20the%20inflation%20data%20could%20be%20especially%20impactful%20for%20stocks%20after%20months%20of%20muted%20reactions%20to%20CPI%20readings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeading%20into%20the%20latest%20inflation%20update%2C%20options%20pricing%20is%20implying%20a%200.64%25%20move%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20which%20would%20mark%20the%20smallest%20CPI-related%20move%20since%20inflation%20began%20rising%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bank.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20economic%20growth%20concerns%20have%20ebbed%20since%20rearing%20their%20head%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20inflation%20appears%20to%20be%20inching%20up%20again.%20The%20strategists%20pointed%20to%20the%20Bloomberg%20Inflation%20Surprise%20Index%2C%20which%20indicates%20that%20the%20most%20recent%20inflation%20data%20marked%20the%20biggest%20upside%20surprise%20to%20CPI%20since%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221033%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Inflation%20concerns%20are%20rising%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675717df8fbb2783ed3092c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221118%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInflation%20concerns%20are%20rising%2C%20with%20price%20increases%20surprising%20more%20to%20the%20upside%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bloomberg%20US%20Inflation%20Surprise%20Index.%3Cp%3EBofA%20Global%20Research%2FBloomberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20that%20backdrop%2C%20we%20believe%20the%20two%20remaining%20major%20events%20of%20the%20year%20(CPI%20and%20FOMC)%20can%20set%20the%20near-term%20direction%20of%20the%20ma