ime.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20it%20involves%20using%20different%20muscle%20groups%20with%20each%20move%2C%20so%20that%20you're%20resting%20your%20legs%20while%20your%20upper%20body%20is%20working%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216ea0a4e-0daf-47ea-a46f-87229d2f7f63%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20'EMOM'%20workout%20keeps%20you%20moving%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFlynn%20said%20he%20often%20uses%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famrap-workout-strength-stamina-benefits-how-to-trainer-advice-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etimed%20workout%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20an%20EMOM%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20%26quot%3Bevery%20minute%20on%20the%20minute.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20it%2C%20set%20a%20running%20clock.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20every%20minute%2C%20complete%20a%20set%20of%20exercise%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E10%20kettlebell%20swings%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3Eor%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E10%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-nba-coach-swears-by-goblet-squat-variation-stronger-core-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoblet%20squats%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERest%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20minute.%20Repeat%20for%2010%20to%2015%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20built-in%20rest%20offers%20some%20time%20to%20recover%20while%20still%20keeping%20up%20the%20pace%20enough%20to%20raise%20your%20heart%20rate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-cardio-without-running-trainer-advice-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecombining%20the%20benefits%20of%20cardio%20and%20strength%20training%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20too%20intense%2C%20try%20an%20alternating%20EMOM%2C%20swapping%20in%20a%20less%20intense%20movement%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-hold-plank-for-longer-strong-core-abs-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20-second%20plank%3C%2Fa%3E%20hold%20for%20every%20other%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20out%20on%20the%20clock%20can%20help%20you%20maintain%20a%20high%20intensity%2C%20burning%20calories%20while%20also%20performing%20strength%20exercises%20so%20you're%20building%20muscle%20to%20burn%20even%20more%20energy%20over%20time%2C%20according%20to%20Flynn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou'd%20be%20better%20off%20in%20terms%20of%20bang%20for%20buck%20performing%20what's%20called%20metabolic%20resistance%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20get%20leaner%20is%20actually%20try%20to%20focus%20on%20being%20stronger%20and%20a%20bit%20more%20muscular%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb6a1567-3753-4add-ad94-32757c6eedfb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKettlebell%20complexes%20combine%20multiple%20exercises%20efficiently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFlynn%20likes%20combining%20movements%20together%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkettlebell-exercises-full-body-workout-strength-training-speed-stamina-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkout%20complex%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20transitioning%20from%20one%20exercise%20to%20the%20next%20without%20putting%20the%20weight%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E5%20single-arm%20kettlebell%20swings%20(with%20one%20kettlebell)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E5%20single-arm%20cleans%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E5%20single-arm%20presses%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E5%20squats%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E5%20lunges%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERepeat%20on%20the%20other%20side%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20complex%20is%20great%20for%20increasing%20your%20intensity%20and%20getting%20work%20done%20in%20less%20time.%20Beginners%20should%20master%20the%20basic%20moves%20first%20before%20trying%20a%20complex%2C%20since%20you%20need%20to%20be%20comfortable%20switching%20seamlessly%20between%20moves%20(and%20sometimes%20doing%20more%20advanced%