ich%20was%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Elskes%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fcanal-group-paddington-studiocanal-stock-exchange-1236243458%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IIT%20Researchers%20Make%20Bacteria%20Eat%20Carbon%20Dioxide%2C%20Methane%20For%20Cleaner%20Fuel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWaste%20to%20wealth%20and%20combating%20climate%20change%2C%20a%20win-win%20laboratory%20scale%20solution%20has%20been%20developed%20by%20scientists%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Guwahati.%20They%20have%20deployed%20a%20bacteria%20to%20help%20them%20achieve%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Debasish%20Das%20and%20Dr%20Krishna%20Kalyani%20Sahoo%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Biosciences%20and%20Bioengineering%2C%20IIT%20Guwahati%2C%20have%20developed%20an%20advanced%20biological%20method%20to%20convert%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20cleaner%20biofuels%20using%20a%20special%20type%20of%20bacteria%20called%20methanotrophic%20(methane-eating)%20%C2%A0bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20nifty%20biological%20sequestration%20route%20is%20the%20discovery%20but%20is%20still%20at%20five%20litre%20laboratory%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Das.%20%26quot%3BThis%20innovative%20approach%20represents%20a%20significant%20leap%20toward%20sustainable%20energy%20solutions%20and%20climate%20change%20mitigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20addresses%20two%20pressing%20global%20challenges%20-%20the%20harmful%20environmental%20impact%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%2C%20and%20the%20depletion%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20reserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMethane%2C%20a%20greenhouse%20gas%20that%20is%2027-30%20times%20more%20potent%20than%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20is%20a%20significant%20contributor%20to%20global%20warming.%20While%20turning%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20liquid%20fuels%20can%20reduce%20emissions%20and%20provide%20renewable%20energy%2C%20existing%20chemical%20methods%20are%20energy-intensive%2C%20expensive%2C%20and%20produce%20toxic%20byproducts%2C%20limiting%20their%20scalability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20research%20is%20a%20breakthrough%20as%20it%20demonstrates%20that%20biomethanol%20derived%20from%20bacteria%20feeding%20on%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20can%20be%20a%20viable%20alternative%20to%20fossil%20fuels%2C%26quot%3B%20professor%20Das%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20conventional%20biofuels%20that%20rely%20on%20crops%20and%20create%20competition%20with%20food%20production%2C%20our%20method%20uses%20greenhouse%20gases%2C%20avoiding%20the%20food%20versus%20fuel%20issue.%20It%20is%20an%20environmentally%20and%20economically%20viable%20solution%2C%20using%20inexpensive%20resources%20while%20contributing%20to%20emissions%20reduction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fs4kf5js8_debasish-das_625x300_09_December_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20laboratory%20of%20professor%20Debasish%20Das%2C%20Department%20of%20Biosciences%20and%20Bioengineering%2C%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Guwahati%20(IIT%20Guwahati)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IIT%20Guwahati%20team%20has%20developed%20a%20fully%20biological%20process%20that%20uses%20a%20soil-borne%20friendly%20microbe%20named%20'Methylosinus%20Trichosporium'%2C%20a%20type%20of%20methane-eating%20bacteria%2C%20to%20convert%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20biomethanol%20under%20special%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20traditional%20chemical%20methods%2C%20this%20process%20eliminates%20the%20need%20for%20expensive%20catalysts%2C%20avoids%20toxic%20byproducts%2C%20and%20operates%20in%20a%20more%20energy-efficient%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20innovative%20two-stage%20process%20involves%20capturing%20methane%20to%20generate%20bacteria-based%20biomass%20and%20using%20the%20biomass%20to%20convert%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20methanol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Das%20and%20his%20team%20subsequently%20took%20it%20forward%20and%20the%20biomethanol%20produced%20in%20their%20laboratory%20was%20blended%20with%20normal%20diesel%20and%20tested%20in%20a%20four-stroke%20diesel%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F4bf2epl8_bacteria-iit-guwahati_625x300_09_December_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20showed%20up%20to%2087%20per%20cent%20reduction%20in%20carbon%20monoxide%2C%20hydrocarbons%2C%20hydrogen%20sulphide%2C%20and%20smoke%20emissions%2C%20and%20improved%20efficiency%20since%20the%20diesel-methanol%20blends%20outperformed%20pure%20diesel%20in%20fuel%20consumption%2C%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20and%20engine%20performance%20while%20maintaining%20similar%20mechanical%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biological%20conversion%20of%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20biomethanol%20not%20only%20provides%20a%20cleaner%20fuel%20alternative%2C%20but%20also%20has%20industrial%20applications%20as%20a%20precursor%20for%20producing%20chemicals%20like%20formaldehyde%20and%20acetic%20acid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Das%20said%20this%20process%20offers%20immense%20potential%20to%20decarbonise%20critical%20industries%2C%20including%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20refineries%2C%20and%20chemical%20manufacturing%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20a%20more%20sustainable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733762460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fmom5fqc_bacteria-iit-guwahati_625x300_09_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia