%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20found%20that%20the%20training%20of%20one%20large%20AI%20language%20model%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Meta's%20Llama%203.1%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0would%20generate%20as%20much%20air%20pollution%20as%20a%20car%20driving%20round-trip%20from%20New%20York%20to%20Los%20Angeles%2010%2C000%20times.%20The%20total%20cost%20of%20AI's%20health%20impacts%2C%20they%20found%2C%20could%20reach%20%2420%20billion%20within%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20the%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Riverside%20and%20the%20California%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20conducted%20what%20they%20say%20may%20be%20the%20first%20study%20of%20its%20kind%20assessing%20AI's%20impacts%20on%20air%20pollution.%20The%20paper%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Unpaid%20Toll%3A%20Quantifying%20the%20Public%20Health%20impact%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20will%20be%20released%20later%20today%2C%20finds%20that%20the%20generation%20of%20electricity%20for%20data%20centers%20hosting%20artificial%20intelligence%20applications%20could%20pollute%20the%20air%20so%20much%20that%20by%202030%20an%20additional%201%2C300%20people%20may%20die%20prematurely%20each%20year%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20a%2036%25%20increase%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Ffastats%2Fasthma.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20annual%20asthma-related%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20%E2%80%94%20led%20by%20Shaolei%20Ren%20of%20UC%20Riverside%20and%20CalTech's%20Adam%20Wierman%20%E2%80%94%20examined%20the%20release%20of%20nitrogen%20dioxide%2C%20sulfur%20dioxide%2C%20and%20particulate%20matter%20with%20a%20diameter%20of%202.5%20micrometers%20or%20less%2C%20which%20can%20penetrate%20deep%20into%20the%20lungs%2C%20by%20power%20plants%20and%20diesel%20generators%20associated%20with%20AI%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boom%20in%20artificial%20intelligence%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20spike%20in%20electricity%20demand.%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20the%20consulting%20firm%2C%20projects%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Findustries%2Fprivate-capital%2Four-insights%2Fhow-data-centers-and-the-energy-sector-can-sate-ais-hunger-for-power%23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20centers%20will%20use%2011%20to%2012%25%20of%20the%20total%20electricity%3C%2Fa%3E%20consumed%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%202030%2C%20up%20from%203%20to%204%25%20last%20year.%20While%20the%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20water%20usage%20implications%20of%20that%20growth%20have%20started%20to%20draw%20scrutiny%2C%20the%20direct%20health%20impacts%20of%20the%20air%20pollution%20these%20facilities%20generate%20have%20been%20mostly%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20something%20like%20this%2C%20air%20pollution%2C%20which%20is%20affecting%20people%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Ren%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20paying%20attention%20to%20it%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20estimate%20that%20the%20generation%20of%20electricity%20for%20AI%20data%20centers%20could%20trigger%20roughly%20600%2C000%20asthma%20symptom%20cases%20a%20year%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimate%2C%20the%20generative%20AI%20boom%20led%20to%20a%20public%20health%20burden%20of%20%245.6%20billion.%20By%202030%2C%20they%20calculated%2C%20AI's%20electricity-related%20public%20health%20costs%20will%20top%20%2420%20billion.%20That's%20more%20than%20double%20the%20public-health%20costs%20of%20coal-based%20US%20steelmaking%2C%20they%20write%2C%20and%20will%20rival%20the%20emissions%20produced%20by%20California's%2035%20million%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20estimates%20are%20based%20on%20a%20risk%20assessment%20tool%20developed%20by%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20that%20assigns%20a%20dollar%20figure%20to%20what%20it%20would%20take%20to%20avoid%20negative%20health%20outcomes%2C%20such%20as%20premature%20deaths%2C%20asthma%20symptoms%2C%20heart%20attacks%2C%20and%20missed%20days%20of%20school%20or%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ren%2C%20whose%20field%20of%20study%20is%20responsible%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20his%20interest%20in%20air%20quality%20dates%20back%20to%20his%20childhood.%20He%20lived%20in%20a%20small%20mining%20town%20in%20China%20until%20the%20age%20of%20six%2C%20where%20he%20saw%20a%20correlation%20between%20poor%20air%20quality%20and%20adverse%20health%20outcomes%20in%20his%20community%2C%20including%20lung%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20is%20what's%20called%20a%20preprint%2C%20a%20standard%20practice%20in%20computer%20science%20research%20in%20which%20researchers%20make%20a%20paper%20public%20before%20submitting%20it%20for%20peer%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f1ba2c9-1959-4084-a2ee-c282087b7860%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiesel%20generators%20appear%20deadly%20in%20Virginia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20examined%20air%20pollution%20driven%20by%20emissions%20from%20diesel%20generators%20used%20by%20data%20centers%20for%20backup%20power%20and%20by%20the%20manufacturing%20of%20the%20silicone%20chips%20used%20in%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20examine%20the%20impact%20of%20diesel-generators%2C%20the%20researchers%20looked%20at%20those%20permitted%20in%20Virginia%2C%20home%20to%20one%20of%20the%20densest%20collections%20of%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20world.%20Generators%2C%20according%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20produce%20200%20to%20600%20times%20the%20nitrogen%20dioxide%20per%20unit%20of%20power%20produced%20than%20a%20natural%20gas%20power%20plant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDiesel%20generators%20represent%20a%20major%20source%20of%20on-site%20air%20pollutants%20for%20data%20centers%20and%20pose%20a%20significant%20health%20risk%20to%20the%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20assuming%20that%20emissions%20by%20Virginia-permitted%20generators%20were%20just%2010%25%20of%20what%20the%20commonwealth's%20regulations%20allow%2C%20they%20would%20cause%20an%20additional%2013%20to%2019%20deaths%20each%20year.%20If%20the%20diesel%20generators%20emitted%20100%25%20of%20what%20is%20allowed%2C%20they%20would%20lead%20to%20130%20to%20190%20additional%20deaths%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20health%20burden%20of%20Virginia's%20data%20center%20generators%20amounts%20to%20%24220%20million%20to%20%24300%20million%20a%20year%20under%20the%2010%25%20assumption%20and%20as%20much%20as%20%243%20billion%20a%20year%20under%20the%20100%25%20assumption%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20those%20health%20effects%20are%20not%20contained%20to%20the%20state%2C%20as%20air%20pollution%20travels.%20They%20found%20it's%20actually%20a%20county%20in%20Maryland%20%E2%80%94%20Montgomery%20County%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%20most%20affected%20by%20Virginia's%20AI%20generators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%2C%20according%20to%20the%20EPA%20tool%2C%20would%20also%20be%20felt%20in%20West%20Virginia%2C%20New%20York%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20Delaware%2CWashington%20D.C.%2C%20and%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20the%20air%20pollution%20was%20limited%20to%20a%20small%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Ren%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20true.%20There%20is%20actually%20cross-state%20air%20pollution.%26quot%3B%20He%20and%20the%20other%20researchers%20found%20that%20the%20harmful%20effects%20are%20felt%20disproportionately%20by%20%26quot%3Beconomically-disadvantaged%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERen%20said%20that%20understanding%20the%20broad%20dispersion%20of%20negative%20health%20outcomes%20could%20encourage%20AI%20companies%20to%20alter%20their%20site%20locations%20or%20AI%20training%20schedules.%20Health%20impacts%20are%20higher%20during%20the%20day%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20some%20locations%20have%20higher%20or%20lower%20health%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20call%20for%20greater%20transparency%20from%20the%20big%20tech%20companies%20that%20lead%20large%20language%20model%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20companies%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Meta%20don't%20currently%20detail%20the%20air%20pollution%20impacts%20of%20their%20AI%20operations%20in%20their%20annual%20sustainability%20reports%2C%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20sustainability%20reports%20from%20these%20companies%2C%20they%20mention%20carbon%20and%20water%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20mention%20anything%20about%20air%20pollution%2C%26quot%3B%20Ren%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20start%20reporting%20this%20in%20the%20same%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-20-billion-dollar-air-pollution-problem-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733762382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67570b5fa57635a3d24d1789%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-20-billion-dollar-air-pollution-problem-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20find%20AI-related%20emissions%20will%20soon%20rival%20that%20of%20all%20the%20cars%20in%20California%20and%20cause%20asthma%20deaths%20to%20spike.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dcampbell%2Bweb%40insider.com%20(Dakin%20Campbell%2CHannah%20Beckler)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-20-billion-dollar-air-pollution-problem-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Foolhardy'%3A%20Former%20pacer%20blasts%20suggestions%20for%20Rohit%20to%20open%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733762260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%